></p><p><b>code</b>: <span title=\"Codes:{http://snomed.info/sct 60600009}, {http://hl7.org/fhir/sid/icd-10 J38.7}\">Muu kurkunpään sairaus</span></p><p><b>subject</b>: <a href=\"Bundle-IpsBundle.html#urn-uuid-b4ac89c5-6589-417f-beef-d3fb1ef9c70f\">Mikael Rinnetmäki</a></p><p><b>onset</b>: 2016-06-14</p><p><b>asserter</b>: Kleemola, Leenamaija</p><p><b>note</b>: By urn:uuid:b4ac89c5-6589-417f-beef-d3fb1ef9c70f</p><blockquote><div><p>I disagree with this diagnosis. The earlier diagnosis of dysphonia due to vocal cord problems is correct. For this diagnosis, I got a prescription for reflux medication, which I did not get. For the earlier diagnosis, I was supposed to get voice therapy, but got this other diagnosis instead. What actually helped was that I started to sing in a choir. Whenever I take a longer break from singing, the symptoms come back. When I start singing again, the symptoms go away.</p>\n</div></blockquote></div>"^^rdf:XMLLiteral ]
